================================================================
THINGS THAT GO WRONG AND HOW TO FIX THEM
================================================================

Nodes show "down" in sinfo:
  - Check slurmd on that worker: systemctl status slurmd
  - Check munge on that worker: systemctl status munge
  - Try: scontrol update nodename=worker1 state=resume

Jobs stuck in PD forever:
  - Run: squeue --reason
  - Common fix: nodes may need resuming (see above)
  - Check slurm.conf CPUs/Memory match the actual hardware

Munge errors:
  - Almost always a munge.key permission issue
  - Fix: chown munge:munge /etc/munge/munge.key && chmod 400 /etc/munge/munge.key
  - Then: systemctl restart munge

NFS mount fails on workers:
  - Check nfs-kernel-server is running on master
  - Check exportfs -v shows the /shared export
  - Check ufw allows NFS from worker IPs

Ganglia not showing data:
  - Check gmond is running on all nodes: systemctl status ganglia-monitor
  - Check gmetad is running on master: systemctl status gmetad
  - Make sure port 8649 UDP is open: ufw allow 8649/udp
  - Wait 2-3 minutes after start for data to populate

Grafana shows no data:
  - Check Prometheus is scraping: http://192.168.1.10:9090/targets
  - All targets should show "UP" in green
  - If a node shows down, check node_exporter is running on it

